    // INDEX — MANTRA
    mantra_title: 'The Mool Mantra',
    mantra_meaning: '"Om Hreem Batukaya Apaduddharanaya Kuru Kuru Batukaya Hreem"<br><em>O Batuk Bhairav, please remove all obstacles and distress from my life.</em>',
    mantra_guide: 'Chant 108 times daily, preferably on Sunday or Tuesday, facing South.',
    btn_copy: 'Copy Mantra',

    // INDEX — KASHI
    kashi_title: 'Kashi — The Eternal City',
    kashi_source: 'Source: Kashi Khanda, Skanda Purana',
    kashi_story_title: 'Why Kaal Bhairav is Kashi\'s Guardian',
    kashi_p1: 'When Lord Shiva decided to make Kashi his permanent abode, he needed an eternal guardian for the city — one who would maintain cosmic order, punish wrongdoers, and ensure that every soul dying within the city\'s limits received liberation (<em>moksha</em>).',
    kashi_p2: 'He appointed <strong class="text-gold">Kaal Bhairav</strong> as the <em>Kotwal</em> — the keeper of Kashi. The Kaal Bhairav temple on Kaal Bhairav Gali in Varanasi is one of the most important shrines in the city, and it is said that one must visit Kaal Bhairav before visiting Kashi Vishwanath — to seek permission to enter the eternal city.',
    kashi_p3: 'According to tradition, even Lord Yama (the god of death) has no authority within the boundaries of Kashi — it is Kaal Bhairav alone who presides over death and liberation here. Every soul departing from Kashi is said to receive the <em>Tarak Mantra</em> whispered in the ear by Lord Shiva himself, through the grace of Kaal Bhairav.',
